{
  "texts": [
    "To understand the statistical patterns within the Rummagene corpus, we performed various exploratory analyses, as well as demonstrate how this rich resource of organized biological knowledge can be used for specific applications.",
    "The initial version of Rummagene contains 642,389 gene sets extracted from 121,237 articles.",
    "These 121,237 articles are identified as containing gene sets from 5,448,589 scanned PMC articles.",
    "The distribution of the occurrence of genes in gene sets is not even.",
    "Some genes are found in many sets, but most genes are members of few sets (Fig. 1a)."
  ]
}